annotationA: Myb-MuvB complex subunit Lin-52; It is involved in the biological process described with: compound eye development; cell cycle; negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter
annotationB: Myb protein; DNA-binding protein that specifically recognizes the sequence 5'-YAAC[GT]G-3'. Component of the DREAM complex, a multiprotein complex that can both act as a transcription activator or repressor depending on the context. In follicle cells, the complex plays a central role in the site-specific DNA replication at the chorion loci. During development, the complex represses transcription of developmentally controlled E2F target genes
